1
00:02:05,909 --> 00:02:07,877
- Hey, fella.
- Huh?

2
00:02:07,911 --> 00:02:09,936
You thinking
of jumping?

3
00:02:09,979 --> 00:02:12,709
- Why, what's it to you?
- Nothing.

4
00:02:12,749 --> 00:02:15,616
- You got any cash?
- Huh?

5
00:02:15,652 --> 00:02:17,847
It's not gonna do you
any good down there.

6
00:02:17,887 --> 00:02:20,583
Oh, for...

7
00:02:24,594 --> 00:02:27,085
Much obliged.

8
00:02:27,130 --> 00:02:29,462
Nice watch.

9
00:02:33,169 --> 00:02:37,105
Thank you.
You have a nice day.

10
00:02:37,140 --> 00:02:40,439
Hey, fella,
it's none of my business,

11
00:02:40,476 --> 00:02:42,842
but you really
picked a lousy spot.

12
00:02:42,879 --> 00:02:45,848
- What are you talking about?
- There's too much traffic.

13
00:02:45,882 --> 00:02:49,249
You jump here,
a car could swerve, cause an accident,

14
00:02:49,285 --> 00:02:50,809
hurt some people.

15
00:02:50,854 --> 00:02:52,822
You'd never
forgive yourself.

16
00:02:52,856 --> 00:02:56,019
Oh, I guess
you're right.

17
00:02:56,059 --> 00:02:59,688
Thank you.
Where would be a good spot?

18
00:02:59,729 --> 00:03:01,754
There's an on-ramp
over there.

19
00:03:01,798 --> 00:03:04,767
I bet it'd be perfect.
I'll show you if you'd like.

20
00:03:04,801 --> 00:03:06,826
Oh, you're
very kind.

21
00:03:14,811 --> 00:03:16,972
See? Isn't this better?

22
00:03:17,013 --> 00:03:19,379
Much better.
Thanks again for your help.

23
00:03:19,415 --> 00:03:20,780
My pleasure.

24
00:03:20,817 --> 00:03:23,615
Hey, you mind
if I watch?

25
00:03:23,653 --> 00:03:25,848
I never saw anyone
do this before.

26
00:03:25,889 --> 00:03:27,857
If it bothers you,
just say so.

27
00:03:27,891 --> 00:03:30,086
- I don't mind.
- Great.

28
00:03:30,126 --> 00:03:33,323
I'll just stay over here.
Give you a little privacy.

29
00:03:51,014 --> 00:03:54,211
- Excuse me.
- What?

30
00:03:54,250 --> 00:03:57,378
I got some other things to do today,
if you're gonna be awhile.

31
00:03:57,420 --> 00:03:58,819
No no no no.

32
00:03:58,855 --> 00:04:00,982
I mean, I could go,
and I could come back.

33
00:04:01,024 --> 00:04:03,288
There's no need for that.

34
00:04:11,668 --> 00:04:14,501
I can't do it.
I cannot do it!

35
00:04:14,537 --> 00:04:17,005
Oh, hell,
who needs this?

36
00:04:17,040 --> 00:04:20,009
Wait wait, look,
I have no place to stay.

37
00:04:20,043 --> 00:04:22,034
No place to go.
I'll need some money.

38
00:04:22,078 --> 00:04:24,046
Hey, what am I,
the Salvation Army?

39
00:04:24,080 --> 00:04:26,378
You need money,
go get a job and earn it.

40
00:04:31,421 --> 00:04:33,514
Come on,
I'll buy you a drink.

41
00:04:37,860 --> 00:04:40,226
So why'd you want
to end it all?

42
00:04:40,263 --> 00:04:43,528
- Nothing to live for.
- You had a hard life?

43
00:04:43,566 --> 00:04:46,262
Not always.

44
00:04:46,302 --> 00:04:49,669
This time last year
I had $10 million.

45
00:04:49,706 --> 00:04:51,765
Oh yeah, sure.

46
00:04:51,808 --> 00:04:53,969
I did.
I had everything.

47
00:04:54,010 --> 00:04:57,070
I had a beautiful home
in Beverly Hills.

48
00:04:57,113 --> 00:05:01,743
Beautiful wife
and a beautiful mistress.

49
00:05:01,784 --> 00:05:05,083
A beautiful dog.

50
00:05:05,121 --> 00:05:08,955
Most beautiful of all,
I had a son, Michael.

51
00:05:08,992 --> 00:05:13,395
He just graduated from college
and was traveling through Europe.

52
00:05:13,429 --> 00:05:15,522
And I had a lot
of good friends.

53
00:05:15,565 --> 00:05:18,261
Aram, you already got
that full house?

54
00:05:18,301 --> 00:05:21,202
lt'll cost you 10
to find out.

55
00:05:21,237 --> 00:05:23,296
I'm out!

56
00:05:23,339 --> 00:05:25,899
Me too.

57
00:05:25,942 --> 00:05:28,934
Aram, I will...

58
00:05:28,978 --> 00:05:31,572
see your 10

59
00:05:31,614 --> 00:05:34,174
and raise you 10.

60
00:05:34,217 --> 00:05:37,948
- Oh, be still my heart.
- I fold.

61
00:05:37,987 --> 00:05:39,614
Now let us see.

62
00:05:39,655 --> 00:05:42,123
He needs a straight
to beat what's showing,

63
00:05:42,158 --> 00:05:45,093
but three eights
were already out.

64
00:05:45,128 --> 00:05:48,256
Now does he have
the necessary eight of spades?

65
00:05:48,297 --> 00:05:51,164
Well, it'll cost you
10 to find out.

66
00:05:51,200 --> 00:05:53,430
Come on, come on.

67
00:05:53,469 --> 00:05:54,868
Wait, I have to
do this logically.

68
00:05:54,904 --> 00:05:57,964
Will you notice Harry
is looking me straight in the eye?

69
00:05:58,007 --> 00:06:01,101
For 20 years, whenever he looked
anybody in the eye, forget it,

70
00:06:01,144 --> 00:06:03,305
he was bluffing.
When he really had the goods,

71
00:06:03,346 --> 00:06:06,440
he just looked down
at his hand.

72
00:06:06,482 --> 00:06:09,007
But a couple of months ago,
he must have figured I was onto him

73
00:06:09,052 --> 00:06:11,680
because he reversed
himself, and ooh, it worked.

74
00:06:11,721 --> 00:06:13,689
He did pretty good
for a couple of weeks.

75
00:06:13,723 --> 00:06:15,691
But last week I realized
what was going on,

76
00:06:15,725 --> 00:06:17,750
and I took him
for a bundle.

77
00:06:17,794 --> 00:06:22,629
So this week, he has
probably reversed himself again,

78
00:06:22,665 --> 00:06:25,395
which should mean
he does not have

79
00:06:25,435 --> 00:06:27,835
the necessary
eight of spades.

80
00:06:27,870 --> 00:06:30,430
Would you please put
your money where your logic is?

81
00:06:30,473 --> 00:06:31,804
All right, all right,
all right.

82
00:06:31,841 --> 00:06:34,571
10 and I raise
you 10.

83
00:06:34,610 --> 00:06:38,376
I will see your 10
and 20 more.

84
00:06:38,414 --> 00:06:42,714
I could be wrong,
but a man has to do

85
00:06:42,752 --> 00:06:44,310
what a man has to do.

86
00:06:44,353 --> 00:06:46,685
- Did you say 20?
- 20.

87
00:06:46,722 --> 00:06:48,690
20 and I will
raise you 30.

88
00:06:48,724 --> 00:06:50,919
Ooh, Harry, the price
of poker just went up.

89
00:06:50,960 --> 00:06:53,793
I will see your 30,
and I will raise you...

90
00:06:53,830 --> 00:06:55,855
one, two, three, four,
five... 50!

91
00:06:55,898 --> 00:06:59,561
I am going to
raise you 100.

92
00:06:59,602 --> 00:07:03,800
100, 100, damn!

93
00:07:08,611 --> 00:07:10,476
I love it.
I love it. I love it.

94
00:07:10,513 --> 00:07:12,845
This could go on
all night.

95
00:07:12,882 --> 00:07:15,180
How could you be sure
he didn't have the eight of spades?

96
00:07:15,218 --> 00:07:17,709
He could have been pulling a double
reverse. He might have had it.

97
00:07:17,753 --> 00:07:21,689
That would have
made two of us.

98
00:07:21,724 --> 00:07:23,157
You bastard, you.

99
00:07:23,192 --> 00:07:26,286
Oh, what a night. Good jokes,
good pastrami, I made a bundle.

100
00:07:26,329 --> 00:07:30,231
And ooh, to top it off, I got
to humiliate one of my closest friends.

101
00:07:30,266 --> 00:07:33,394
It doesn't get
better than this.

102
00:07:33,636 --> 00:07:36,332
I had a thriving business.

103
00:07:36,372 --> 00:07:39,364
A business I built up from nothing,
that I was very proud of.

104
00:07:39,408 --> 00:07:41,808
I had a dozen stores,

105
00:07:41,844 --> 00:07:44,642
but I treated each
as if it were the only one.

106
00:07:56,592 --> 00:08:00,028
Come in.

107
00:08:00,062 --> 00:08:01,962
Sir, what can
I do for you?

108
00:08:06,602 --> 00:08:09,662
Mr. Katourian, you're on another
inspection tour, I see.

109
00:08:09,705 --> 00:08:12,606
No no, Mr. Macrae.
I don't inspect. I spy.

110
00:08:12,642 --> 00:08:14,940
I spy on box boys,
butchers, checkers.

111
00:08:14,977 --> 00:08:17,411
What I spy
with my little eye,

112
00:08:17,446 --> 00:08:19,971
I do not like,
Mr. Macrae.

113
00:08:20,016 --> 00:08:22,450
- Problem?
- Yes, a problem.

114
00:08:22,485 --> 00:08:24,680
A problem with the supervision
of this supermarket.

115
00:08:24,720 --> 00:08:27,382
Do you follow baseball,
Mr. Macrae?

116
00:08:27,423 --> 00:08:29,550
- A little.
- Strike one.

117
00:08:29,592 --> 00:08:31,583
I asked a clerk
in the vegetable section,

118
00:08:31,627 --> 00:08:33,254
"Where are the fresh
chick-peas?"

119
00:08:33,296 --> 00:08:35,821
Without looking up, he said,
"Three aisles over to your left."

120
00:08:35,865 --> 00:08:38,231
In a Katourian market,
when a customer asks

121
00:08:38,267 --> 00:08:40,428
the location of an item,
what should happen?

122
00:08:40,469 --> 00:08:42,869
The employee should personally
take the customer

123
00:08:42,905 --> 00:08:46,602
to the desired item.
I tell the staff regularly

124
00:08:46,642 --> 00:08:48,303
- that it's their job...
- Strike two.

125
00:08:48,344 --> 00:08:51,836
I had to wait behind five customers
at the checkout counter.

126
00:08:51,881 --> 00:08:53,849
At a Katourian
checkout counter,

127
00:08:53,883 --> 00:08:56,681
what happens when three
or more customers form a line?

128
00:08:56,719 --> 00:08:59,813
Another counter is opened. The
vegetables arrived late this morning.

129
00:08:59,855 --> 00:09:03,256
- I told the staff...
- How are eggs bagged, Mr. Macrae?

130
00:09:03,292 --> 00:09:05,260
Always on top of the bag,
of course.

131
00:09:05,294 --> 00:09:07,262
Staff knows that.
Otherwise, they get broken.

132
00:09:07,296 --> 00:09:10,026
Would you find the eggs
in that bag, please?

133
00:09:22,478 --> 00:09:24,503
Strike three.

134
00:09:24,547 --> 00:09:26,310
Mr. Katourian...

135
00:09:26,349 --> 00:09:29,341
Mr. Macrae I do not procure the finest
organically grown eggs

136
00:09:29,385 --> 00:09:32,218
from the finest organically grown
chickens so that my customers

137
00:09:32,255 --> 00:09:35,986
can find an organically grown mess
at the bottom of their shopping bags.

138
00:09:38,527 --> 00:09:40,324
Go ahead.

139
00:09:40,363 --> 00:09:42,695
- Yes.
- Is Mr. Katourian there?

140
00:09:42,732 --> 00:09:45,098
Yes, he's here.

141
00:09:46,636 --> 00:09:48,126
- Hello.
- Aram.

142
00:09:48,170 --> 00:09:50,502
- Oh, yes, Millie.
- Michael called.

143
00:09:50,539 --> 00:09:52,803
- Oh, he did, Michael called?
- I just talked to him.

144
00:09:52,842 --> 00:09:54,776
- Where from?
- The airport.

145
00:09:54,810 --> 00:09:57,142
The airport here in LA?
He's home?

146
00:09:57,179 --> 00:09:59,204
- Yes.
- Tell him to wait there, I'll get him.

147
00:09:59,248 --> 00:10:02,740
- No, he's taking a taxi.
- He's okay? He sounds all right?

148
00:10:02,785 --> 00:10:05,618
- He's fine.
- Good, I'll be right home.

149
00:10:08,124 --> 00:10:10,684
Macrae, keep up
the good work.

150
00:10:10,726 --> 00:10:12,353
Yes, sir.

151
00:10:14,530 --> 00:10:17,363
- Good disguise, huh?
- One of your best.

152
00:10:29,745 --> 00:10:33,875
Oh, Michael, oh!

153
00:10:33,916 --> 00:10:36,544
There he is!

154
00:10:36,585 --> 00:10:38,780
Hey, wave at the camera.
Wave at the camera!

155
00:10:38,821 --> 00:10:42,086
- Face the camera.
- Dad! Hi, Dad!

156
00:10:42,124 --> 00:10:44,354
- Hi, Dad!
- Still going, still going.

157
00:10:44,393 --> 00:10:48,523
There we go.
It's so good to see you, son.

158
00:10:48,564 --> 00:10:50,794
Hey, this is Bob.
Dad, Mom... Bob.

159
00:10:50,833 --> 00:10:53,734
Do me a favor.
Could you hold that camera there?

160
00:10:55,738 --> 00:10:57,706
Get on that side.
Here we go.

161
00:10:57,740 --> 00:10:59,708
Point it at us.
That's it.

162
00:10:59,742 --> 00:11:03,007
Up a little, I think. Can you see
all three? Okay. There we go.

163
00:11:05,548 --> 00:11:09,279
Wonder if Michael gave any thought
to a career while he was away.

164
00:11:09,318 --> 00:11:11,377
Why didn't you ask him?

165
00:11:11,420 --> 00:11:13,388
I didn't want
to pressure him.

166
00:11:13,422 --> 00:11:15,686
You know,
first night home.

167
00:11:15,725 --> 00:11:17,989
I didn't want him to feel like he's
gotta get up tomorrow

168
00:11:18,027 --> 00:11:20,222
and start looking
for a job.

169
00:11:20,262 --> 00:11:25,165
Very important decision
what a young man does with his life.

170
00:11:25,201 --> 00:11:27,192
I don't wanna
push him.

171
00:11:44,820 --> 00:11:46,811
Yes, sir.

172
00:12:01,470 --> 00:12:03,768
Again, the pool.

173
00:12:03,806 --> 00:12:06,070
He was there when I went to work
this morning.

174
00:12:07,376 --> 00:12:09,344
He didn't spend
all day lying there, did he?

175
00:12:09,378 --> 00:12:11,972
No, he had a friend
over and they played some tennis.

176
00:12:12,014 --> 00:12:15,575
Tennis, good.

177
00:12:15,618 --> 00:12:18,644
It's funny.
I can't understand it.

178
00:12:18,687 --> 00:12:20,655
I mean,
it's been 10 days.

179
00:12:20,689 --> 00:12:22,657
When I was his age,
I had three jobs.

180
00:12:22,691 --> 00:12:24,659
I was taking
a night course

181
00:12:24,693 --> 00:12:26,661
in business
administration,

182
00:12:26,695 --> 00:12:29,129
knocking myself out trying to get
somewhere in the world.

183
00:12:29,165 --> 00:12:31,360
You should talk to him.
You never talk to him.

184
00:12:31,400 --> 00:12:33,368
Hey, this has
to come from him.

185
00:12:33,402 --> 00:12:35,870
If he wants to try
to make something of himself,

186
00:12:35,905 --> 00:12:37,930
it has to be because
he wanted to do it.

187
00:12:37,973 --> 00:12:41,067
And he will.
That I know.

188
00:12:41,110 --> 00:12:42,805
You want him
to be like you, Aram?

189
00:12:42,845 --> 00:12:45,109
No, I don't want him
to be like me.

190
00:12:46,649 --> 00:12:48,776
I just don't want him
to be like him.

191
00:12:53,556 --> 00:12:56,457
Hey.

192
00:12:56,492 --> 00:13:00,485
- Hey!
- Hey, Dad, how you doing?

193
00:13:00,529 --> 00:13:02,759
Fine fine.
How are you doing?

194
00:13:02,798 --> 00:13:04,857
- Great.
- Good.

195
00:13:04,900 --> 00:13:08,028
- Good party last night?
- That was the night before.

196
00:13:08,070 --> 00:13:10,595
Went to a concert
last night with my friend Linda.

197
00:13:10,639 --> 00:13:13,506
- Oh, Linda. Rock concert, right.
- Yeah.

198
00:13:13,542 --> 00:13:17,103
Party was okay.
Concert was a little disappointing.

199
00:13:17,146 --> 00:13:19,376
That's too bad.

200
00:13:19,415 --> 00:13:21,280
And a baseball game
tonight.

201
00:13:21,317 --> 00:13:23,683
No no, change of plans. Some friends
are going to The Comedy Store.

202
00:13:23,719 --> 00:13:27,712
- They asked me to go.
- Busy busy busy.

203
00:13:27,756 --> 00:13:30,520
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

204
00:13:30,559 --> 00:13:33,084
- Dad, what time is it?
- 6:00

205
00:13:33,128 --> 00:13:35,187
I think I'll go in
and take a nap for an hour

206
00:13:35,231 --> 00:13:38,428
before I get dressed.
Kinda sleepy.

207
00:13:38,467 --> 00:13:41,027
Got to bed late
last night, huh?

208
00:13:41,070 --> 00:13:43,038
Yeah, then Shaggy
woke me up at 6:00 in the morning.

209
00:13:43,072 --> 00:13:44,937
I couldn't get
back to sleep.

210
00:13:44,974 --> 00:13:48,034
Yeah, he always barks
when I'm driving away.

211
00:13:48,077 --> 00:13:51,137
- I'll try to keep him quiet.
- Thanks, Dad.

212
00:14:04,693 --> 00:14:08,094
Price check on four,
please.

213
00:14:20,042 --> 00:14:24,479
Young man, could you
tell me which melon is the ripest?

214
00:14:24,513 --> 00:14:26,538
I think you'll find
this is the sweet one.

215
00:14:26,582 --> 00:14:28,550
The texture is nice
and rough,

216
00:14:28,584 --> 00:14:30,552
and you can even hear
a little liquid.

217
00:14:30,586 --> 00:14:33,487
- It should be just right.
- Thank you. You do your job very well.

218
00:14:33,522 --> 00:14:35,490
Well, thank you,
Mr. Katourian.

219
00:14:35,524 --> 00:14:37,822
- I should have worn the false eyebrows.
- No, I saw you

220
00:14:37,860 --> 00:14:40,829
rearranging the tomatoes
when you thought no one was looking.

221
00:14:40,863 --> 00:14:42,956
I'd heard stories about you.
I put two and two together.

222
00:14:42,998 --> 00:14:45,728
- What's your name?
- Steve Harrison.

223
00:14:45,768 --> 00:14:48,134
Steve, you're a very
bright young man, Steve.

224
00:14:48,170 --> 00:14:51,435
I think maybe you're ready to handle
a more responsible position.

225
00:14:51,473 --> 00:14:54,465
- The Northridge branch...
- That's very kind of you.

226
00:14:54,510 --> 00:14:56,671
But I'm leaving next week.
I'm going back to school.

227
00:14:56,712 --> 00:14:58,680
I just took a semester off
to earn some money.

228
00:14:58,714 --> 00:15:00,944
- What are you studying?
- Architecture.

229
00:15:00,983 --> 00:15:03,042
Oh, architecture,
that's a wonderful field.

230
00:15:03,085 --> 00:15:05,883
Well, I'm sure you'll succeed
at whatever you do.

231
00:15:05,921 --> 00:15:07,946
- Thank you.
- Good luck, Steve.

232
00:15:10,459 --> 00:15:12,791
I'll bet your parents are very
proud of you.

233
00:15:12,828 --> 00:15:14,887
I hope so.

234
00:15:19,168 --> 00:15:21,830
Price check from produce,
please.

235
00:15:27,610 --> 00:15:29,578
What's he doing?

236
00:15:29,612 --> 00:15:32,911
Michael?
He's by the pool.

237
00:15:32,948 --> 00:15:34,916
What could be going on
in the boy's head?

238
00:15:34,950 --> 00:15:36,918
He's been out of college
for six months.

239
00:15:36,952 --> 00:15:39,216
There's not been
one word about a job.

240
00:15:39,254 --> 00:15:41,848
What's he wanna be,
a bum all his life?

241
00:15:41,890 --> 00:15:43,858
I have to speak
