I gotta tell you.

1189
01:07:52,551 --> 01:07:55,281
I don't have the guts
to do it to your face.

1190
01:07:55,321 --> 01:07:57,551
I didn't go bankrupt.

1191
01:07:57,590 --> 01:08:00,058
I gave my money away.

1192
01:08:01,427 --> 01:08:04,396
See, I thought
I could turn my son into a man

1193
01:08:04,430 --> 01:08:06,796
and I thought I could turn myself
into a kid again,

1194
01:08:06,832 --> 01:08:09,562
and I couldn't
do either.

1195
01:08:09,602 --> 01:08:11,570
It's a te...

1196
01:08:11,604 --> 01:08:13,868
no no, Shaggy,
go away right now, please.

1197
01:08:13,906 --> 01:08:16,875
It's a terrible thing
that I've done to you, Millie.

1198
01:08:16,909 --> 01:08:19,469
I stole your
whole life away.

1199
01:08:19,512 --> 01:08:21,480
I thought I could
give it back to you

1200
01:08:21,514 --> 01:08:24,347
anytime I wanted,
and I couldn't.

1201
01:08:25,384 --> 01:08:27,352
And I cannot

1202
01:08:27,386 --> 01:08:29,479
stay here
day after day

1203
01:08:29,522 --> 01:08:31,956
looking at the results
of my stupidity,

1204
01:08:31,991 --> 01:08:34,221
and I do not have
the right to forbid you

1205
01:08:34,260 --> 01:08:36,228
from taking
Michael's help.

1206
01:08:36,262 --> 01:08:38,230
God, let him...
let him look after you

1207
01:08:38,264 --> 01:08:41,495
the way that you deserve
to be looked after.

1208
01:08:41,534 --> 01:08:43,525
And...

1209
01:08:46,839 --> 01:08:48,830
you're a wonderful
woman...

1210
01:08:51,076 --> 01:08:53,476
and I'm not worthy
of you.

1211
01:08:54,847 --> 01:08:57,213
Goodbye.

1212
01:08:58,617 --> 01:09:00,141
Oh.

1213
01:09:08,394 --> 01:09:10,362
Boy, that's really
rough.

1214
01:09:10,396 --> 01:09:12,364
That's when you found me
on the overpass.

1215
01:09:12,398 --> 01:09:14,764
- I should have jumped.
- No, don't say that.

1216
01:09:14,800 --> 01:09:16,825
If you had, I wouldn't have
gotten to know you.

1217
01:09:16,869 --> 01:09:18,837
I wouldn't have
heard your story.

1218
01:09:18,871 --> 01:09:21,362
Anyway, I love
a good cry.

1219
01:09:21,407 --> 01:09:24,376
Hey, I got kind of
a confession to make.

1220
01:09:24,410 --> 01:09:26,901
When I told you
that I knew some of the guys

1221
01:09:26,946 --> 01:09:28,914
that you gave
that money to,

1222
01:09:28,948 --> 01:09:30,745
- that wasn't the whole truth.
- No?

1223
01:09:30,783 --> 01:09:32,751
- I was one of the guys.
- Huh?

1224
01:09:32,785 --> 01:09:35,913
I was afraid if I told
you you might put the touch on me.

1225
01:09:35,955 --> 01:09:37,946
You mean, there's
some of it left?

1226
01:09:37,990 --> 01:09:39,617
I got most of it.
In a bank.

1227
01:09:39,658 --> 01:09:41,148
What are you
saving it for?

1228
01:09:41,193 --> 01:09:43,821
For when times
get rough.

1229
01:09:43,863 --> 01:09:45,558
Look,

1230
01:09:45,598 --> 01:09:47,930
it kills me to part
with even a dime.

1231
01:09:47,967 --> 01:09:51,494
I just can't do it.
That's just the way I am, all right?

1232
01:09:51,537 --> 01:09:55,303
But maybe I could let you have
a couple of hundred?

1233
01:09:55,341 --> 01:09:57,673
That's very good of you.

1234
01:09:57,710 --> 01:09:59,644
Good?
I'm a goddamn saint!

1235
01:09:59,678 --> 01:10:02,374
But what the hell,
and I'll tell you what,

1236
01:10:02,414 --> 01:10:04,382
- I'll buy you dinner.
- Yeah?

1237
01:10:04,416 --> 01:10:06,441
Yeah, we'll go someplace
really great, huh?

1238
01:10:06,485 --> 01:10:08,453
- Like maybe Denny's?
- Yeah.

1239
01:10:08,487 --> 01:10:11,354
- Or you got another idea?
- Oh, there's a Chinese restaurant

1240
01:10:11,390 --> 01:10:13,187
that I would love
to go to. Yeah.

1241
01:10:13,225 --> 01:10:14,852
I haven't been there
in a long time.

1242
01:10:14,894 --> 01:10:16,794
Mmm, wow,

1243
01:10:16,829 --> 01:10:18,854
that was one of the best
meals I've ever had.

1244
01:10:18,898 --> 01:10:20,991
Yeah.

1245
01:10:21,033 --> 01:10:23,092
What's the matter?
You didn't like the food?

1246
01:10:23,135 --> 01:10:25,103
Oh hell yeah,
I liked the food.

1247
01:10:25,137 --> 01:10:28,163
I loved it.
The damn food was great.

1248
01:10:28,207 --> 01:10:31,108
On special occasions,
I used to come here with my wife

1249
01:10:31,143 --> 01:10:33,509
when I was feeling
very proud of myself, you know,

1250
01:10:33,545 --> 01:10:35,979
made a big sale,
closed a deal, whatever.

1251
01:10:36,015 --> 01:10:39,041
I always thought
that what made these dinners so great

1252
01:10:39,084 --> 01:10:41,018
was how good I felt
about myself.

1253
01:10:41,053 --> 01:10:43,317
- You see?
- No.

1254
01:10:43,355 --> 01:10:46,483
Well, I never thought
that I could enjoy anything

1255
01:10:46,525 --> 01:10:49,050
unless I really earned it.
Otherwise I'd feel guilty.

1256
01:10:49,094 --> 01:10:50,527
Ah.

1257
01:10:50,562 --> 01:10:52,792
So I figured if the food
tasted that good,

1258
01:10:52,831 --> 01:10:55,959
- it's because I earned it.
- Oh.

1259
01:10:56,001 --> 01:10:58,526
- That wasn't it at all.
- Oh.

1260
01:10:58,570 --> 01:11:01,004
This meal is being paid for
by a lovely lady

1261
01:11:01,040 --> 01:11:04,203
who lives in a cardboard box.
It's every bit as good.

1262
01:11:04,243 --> 01:11:06,837
The damn food
is just great.

1263
01:11:06,879 --> 01:11:09,279
Yeah well,
there was a lot

1264
01:11:09,315 --> 01:11:11,545
of good stuff in the world
before you came along,

1265
01:11:11,583 --> 01:11:14,108
and there'll be
a lot of good stuff after you've gone.

1266
01:11:14,153 --> 01:11:16,519
The trick is to grab some
while you're here.

1267
01:11:18,223 --> 01:11:20,191
You're a very wise
derelict.

1268
01:11:20,225 --> 01:11:21,749
Thank you.

1269
01:11:28,367 --> 01:11:30,801
- Okay.
- Where are you headed?

1270
01:11:30,836 --> 01:11:32,861
As far as that
bus is going.

1271
01:11:32,905 --> 01:11:35,373
You know, I would go with you,
but I really like LA.

1272
01:11:35,407 --> 01:11:37,375
- Yeah?
- I wouldn't feel at home

1273
01:11:37,409 --> 01:11:39,343
being homeless
anywhere else.

1274
01:11:39,378 --> 01:11:41,869
Bye, Billie.

1275
01:11:41,914 --> 01:11:44,883
Bus number 67 serving
the route to San Diego

1276
01:11:44,917 --> 01:11:47,408
- arriving at gate 9.
- Thanks for all your help.

1277
01:11:48,754 --> 01:11:51,689
Hey, wait a minute.
I got something for you.

1278
01:11:51,724 --> 01:11:53,692
Here's your watch.

1279
01:11:53,726 --> 01:11:55,819
Thank you.

1280
01:12:54,953 --> 01:12:56,921
Five, 10, 20.

1281
01:12:56,955 --> 01:12:59,515
- Thank you. Have a nice day.
- Thank you.

1282
01:13:04,363 --> 01:13:06,354
Hello, Millie.

1283
01:13:16,208 --> 01:13:18,540
I went by the apartment.

1284
01:13:18,577 --> 01:13:20,374
I didn't know
you'd moved.

1285
01:13:20,412 --> 01:13:22,380
Mrs. Villalobos told me
I'd find you here.

1286
01:13:22,414 --> 01:13:24,382
You look wonderful.

1287
01:13:24,416 --> 01:13:26,407
Oh, thank you.

1288
01:13:28,187 --> 01:13:30,155
How are you?

1289
01:13:30,189 --> 01:13:32,157
Eh? Fine.

1290
01:13:32,191 --> 01:13:34,659
You got my letters?

1291
01:13:34,693 --> 01:13:37,924
Yeah, from all over
the country.

1292
01:13:37,963 --> 01:13:41,364
But I'm not so sure
an envelope with no address

1293
01:13:41,400 --> 01:13:44,267
containing only some money
wrapped in a blank sheet of paper

1294
01:13:44,303 --> 01:13:48,034
could be called a letter,
but thank you for the money.

1295
01:13:48,073 --> 01:13:50,041
It's not much, I know,

1296
01:13:50,075 --> 01:13:52,009
but whenever I had
any to spare...

1297
01:13:52,044 --> 01:13:54,012
Oh...

1298
01:13:54,046 --> 01:13:55,741
it was nice
you thought of me.

1299
01:13:56,748 --> 01:13:58,579
It would have been nice

1300
01:13:58,617 --> 01:14:01,051
if I had known
what you were doing.

1301
01:14:01,086 --> 01:14:03,577
Nothing really
worth talking about.

1302
01:14:03,622 --> 01:14:05,920
I'd find a job
of some kind,

1303
01:14:05,958 --> 01:14:09,291
make a little money,
and then quit the job, relax a bit,

1304
01:14:09,328 --> 01:14:12,593
move on somewhere else,
take another job, and so on.

1305
01:14:12,631 --> 01:14:14,599
It's hard for me

1306
01:14:14,633 --> 01:14:17,397
to picture you
ever relaxing.

1307
01:14:17,436 --> 01:14:20,064
What did you do
when you weren't working?

1308
01:14:20,105 --> 01:14:23,506
Sit in a park
and feed a pigeon.

1309
01:14:23,542 --> 01:14:25,510
Read a book.

1310
01:14:25,544 --> 01:14:27,512
Visit a zoo,
Grand Canyon.

1311
01:14:27,546 --> 01:14:29,514
What about you?

1312
01:14:29,548 --> 01:14:31,516
Isn't Michael
taking care of you?

1313
01:14:31,550 --> 01:14:34,383
- Why are you still working?
- I enjoy it.

1314
01:14:34,419 --> 01:14:35,818
Oh.

1315
01:14:35,854 --> 01:14:37,879
The boss
treat you okay?

1316
01:14:40,359 --> 01:14:43,419
Aram, I am the boss.

1317
01:14:43,462 --> 01:14:47,023
Oh, isn't that
wonderful!

1318
01:14:47,065 --> 01:14:49,033
Michael bought this
for you?

1319
01:14:49,067 --> 01:14:51,592
No no, I never
took money from Michael.

1320
01:14:51,637 --> 01:14:53,605
I wanted
to look after myself.

1321
01:14:53,639 --> 01:14:55,869
- Then how...
- I have a partner

1322
01:14:55,908 --> 01:14:57,876
who put up
the initial investment.

1323
01:14:57,910 --> 01:15:00,401
- Oh, is it anybody I know?
- Oh yes.

1324
01:15:02,848 --> 01:15:04,816
What's going on here?

1325
01:15:04,850 --> 01:15:07,250
Oh, don't worry.
It's not "This is Your Life."

1326
01:15:07,286 --> 01:15:09,117
- How...
- After you left,

1327
01:15:09,154 --> 01:15:11,122
and I didn't hear
a thing for two months,

1328
01:15:11,156 --> 01:15:14,057
I didn't know if you were alive,
so I went to see Irene

1329
01:15:14,092 --> 01:15:16,959
- to see if she knew anything.
- You knew about Irene?

1330
01:15:16,995 --> 01:15:19,429
I knew about Irene.

1331
01:15:19,464 --> 01:15:21,489
How long?

1332
01:15:21,533 --> 01:15:24,331
Oh, a few years.

1333
01:15:24,369 --> 01:15:26,337
You never said
a word to me.

1334
01:15:26,371 --> 01:15:28,339
The night
before I got married

1335
01:15:28,373 --> 01:15:30,341
my grandmother
came to my room.

1336
01:15:30,375 --> 01:15:32,343
She told me
there were three things

1337
01:15:32,377 --> 01:15:34,345
even God
could not create...

1338
01:15:34,379 --> 01:15:35,812
a floor
that would stay clean,

1339
01:15:35,847 --> 01:15:37,371
a baby
that would stay dry

1340
01:15:37,416 --> 01:15:39,646
and a husband
that would stay faithful.

1341
01:15:39,685 --> 01:15:41,880
Oh.

1342
01:15:43,155 --> 01:15:46,022
Very wise,
your grandmother.

1343
01:15:46,058 --> 01:15:48,686
Anyway, when I didn't hear from you,
I went to see Irene.

1344
01:15:48,727 --> 01:15:51,252
And she was as worried as I was,
and we started talking

1345
01:15:51,296 --> 01:15:53,025
and we found
we liked each other.

1346
01:15:53,065 --> 01:15:55,090
We agreed you had
excellent taste in women.

1347
01:15:55,133 --> 01:15:56,998
One day
I invited her over

1348
01:15:57,035 --> 01:15:59,765
to the apartment for coffee
and I baked my cherry strudel.

1349
01:15:59,805 --> 01:16:01,932
- Oh, it was incredible!
- I know.

1350
01:16:01,974 --> 01:16:03,942
Oh yeah, of course.

1351
01:16:03,976 --> 01:16:06,444
And Irene got the idea
of opening up a shop.

1352
01:16:06,478 --> 01:16:08,946
I took out a mortgage on the condo,
and here we are.

1353
01:16:08,981 --> 01:16:12,473
The shop is doing well?

1354
01:16:12,517 --> 01:16:14,485
We have branches
in Westwood, Encino,

1355
01:16:14,519 --> 01:16:16,646
we're opening another
in Pacific Palisades,

1356
01:16:16,688 --> 01:16:18,883
and there's a group of investors
talking to us

1357
01:16:18,924 --> 01:16:21,154
about opening a national
franchise operation.

1358
01:16:21,193 --> 01:16:23,161
What?

1359
01:16:23,195 --> 01:16:25,459
I wanted to make a man
of my son, not my wife.

1360
01:16:29,534 --> 01:16:31,900
Aram, why did you
come back?

1361
01:16:31,937 --> 01:16:34,599
Pick up the invoice
for me, will you?

1362
01:16:37,276 --> 01:16:39,244
It occurred to me

1363
01:16:39,278 --> 01:16:43,180
that you might want
to end the marriage formally.

1364
01:16:43,215 --> 01:16:45,911
So I'm here to do
whatever you want me to do.

1365
01:16:45,951 --> 01:16:47,919
That's very considerate.

1366
01:16:47,953 --> 01:16:49,921
Is there...

1367
01:16:51,957 --> 01:16:53,652
anyone in your life
right now?

1368
01:16:53,692 --> 01:16:55,660
No no, not really.

1369
01:16:55,694 --> 01:16:57,662
Every time I start
to think about someone,

1370
01:16:57,696 --> 01:17:00,426
an envelope would come
from Buffalo or Wichita

1371
01:17:00,465 --> 01:17:02,433
with $15 or $20 in it,
and l...

1372
01:17:02,467 --> 01:17:05,436
it confused the issue.

1373
01:17:07,673 --> 01:17:09,664
Is there anyone
in your...

1374
01:17:10,742 --> 01:17:13,074
No, it's okay.
You can ask her.

1375
01:17:13,111 --> 01:17:15,079
Ask me what?

1376
01:17:15,113 --> 01:17:17,081
Is there anyone
in your life?

1377
01:17:17,115 --> 01:17:19,379
Yes, there is,
an actor.

1378
01:17:19,418 --> 01:17:21,386
Oh.

1379
01:17:21,420 --> 01:17:24,014
Been in anything
I've seen?

1380
01:17:24,056 --> 01:17:26,024
Just my bedroom.

1381
01:17:26,058 --> 01:17:28,492
He's a lot younger than I am,
and he's poor.

1382
01:17:28,527 --> 01:17:32,054
I find the combination
irresistible.

1383
01:17:32,097 --> 01:17:34,065
Irene, we have to hurry.

1384
01:17:34,099 --> 01:17:36,067
Oh, Millie,
how is Michael?

1385
01:17:36,101 --> 01:17:38,160
Oh, he's fine.
Look, Irene and I have to meet

1386
01:17:38,203 --> 01:17:40,831
the architects at the new shop.
Here's my home address.

1387
01:17:40,872 --> 01:17:43,670
Come over to the house
for dinner about 6:00 and we'll talk.

1388
01:17:43,709 --> 01:17:45,677
Oh good, yeah.

1389
01:17:45,711 --> 01:17:47,736
Well, I'm very happy
things are working out

1390
01:17:47,779 --> 01:17:50,748
- so well for both of you.
- In a way, we owe it all to you.

1391
01:17:50,782 --> 01:17:53,182
Millie and I never would have met
if you hadn't been

1392
01:17:53,218 --> 01:17:55,948
the rotten cheating
bastard that you are.

1393
01:17:55,987 --> 01:17:58,922
- Uh-huh.
- See you at 6:00.

1394
01:17:58,957 --> 01:18:01,187
Heather, we'll be back
in a few hours.

1395
01:18:01,226 --> 01:18:02,955
Oh okay, Mrs. Katourian.

1396
01:18:24,549 --> 01:18:26,517
Hi, Millie.

1397
01:18:26,551 --> 01:18:28,542
Hi.

1398
01:18:30,222 --> 01:18:32,190
All this
from cherry strudel?

1399
01:18:32,224 --> 01:18:34,784
Oh, this isn't mine.
I'm just renting the guest house

1400
01:18:34,826 --> 01:18:37,386
until I can find
a place of my own.

1401
01:18:37,429 --> 01:18:39,397
I was planning
to cook dinner,

1402
01:18:39,431 --> 01:18:42,059
but I didn't have any time to shop,
so if you don't mind,

1403
01:18:42,100 --> 01:18:44,728
- I thought we'd eat out.
- Good, fine.

1404
01:18:52,077 --> 01:18:54,409
Tell me about Michael.
Is he happy?

1405
01:18:54,446 --> 01:18:56,414
What did you say?

1406
01:18:56,448 --> 01:18:58,848
Michael and his new bride,
are they happy together?

1407
01:18:58,884 --> 01:19:00,943
No, I'm afraid not.

1408
01:19:00,986 --> 01:19:02,954
Linda met
a baseball player

1409
01:19:02,988 --> 01:19:05,718
and fell head over heals
and she and Michael got a divorce.

1410
01:19:05,757 --> 01:19:09,318
Oh my God.
Is he all right?

1411
01:19:09,361 --> 01:19:11,659
He was pretty broken up.
He really loved her a lot,

1412
01:19:11,696 --> 01:19:13,721
but he's adjusting.

1413
01:19:13,765 --> 01:19:16,928
Oh Lord.
Where is he living?

1414
01:19:16,968 --> 01:19:19,061
- Here.
- Oh, with you?

1415
01:19:19,104 --> 01:19:22,232
No, it's his house.

1416
01:19:24,409 --> 01:19:27,742
- His house?
- It was part of the divorce settlement.

1417
01:19:27,779 --> 01:19:30,475
Part of the...
what do you mean, "part"?

1418
01:19:30,515 --> 01:19:33,109
He also got
$5 million.

1419
01:19:33,151 --> 01:19:36,211
$5 million?

1420
01:19:36,254 --> 01:19:38,779
Aram, please don't be angry with him.
His lawyer said

1421
01:19:38,824 --> 01:19:42,191
he could have gotten 10 time that,
and he didn't want to take anything.

1422
01:19:42,227 --> 01:19:45,492
And Linda pleaded with him to take it,
because she was feeling very guilty

1423
01:19:45,530 --> 01:19:48,021
about what she was doing.
Don't be angry with Michael.

1424
01:19:48,066 --> 01:19:50,034
I'm not angry.

1425
01:19:50,068 --> 01:19:52,468
I am delighted for him.
Good for him.

1426
01:19:52,504 --> 01:19:54,199
Even though
he didn't earn it?

1427
01:19:54,239 --> 01:19:57,265
If a man wins $50 million in a lottery,
did he earn it?

1428
01:19:57,309 --> 01:19:59,470
As your son would say,
money is money,

1429
01:19:59,511 --> 01:20:01,479
and God bless him,
let him enjoy it.

1430
01:20:01,513 --> 01:20:03,572
Even though it came
from a woman?

1431
01:20:03,615 --> 01:20:06,812
Don't women get money
from men in divorce settlements, Millie?

1432
01:20:06,852 --> 01:20:09,252
What, are you becoming
a sexist pig?

1433
01:20:15,360 --> 01:20:17,658
You know, Millie,
I'm not really proud of the way

1434
01:20:17,696 --> 01:20:20,995
Michael turned out.
I'm not gonna kid myself about that.

1435
01:20:21,032 --> 01:20:23,000
But I have come
to realize

1436
01:20:23,034 --> 01:20:25,935
you don't have to be proud
of someone to love them.

1437
01:20:27,072 --> 01:20:29,040
Is he home?
I'm dying to see him.

1438
01:20:29,074 --> 01:20:32,703
Oh no, he usually doesn't get home
until past midnight.

1439
01:20:32,744 --> 01:20:35,144
- Oh.
- Yeah.

1440
01:20:35,180 --> 01:20:37,546
Oh, uh...

1441
01:20:37,582 --> 01:20:39,550
have you given
any thought

1442
01:20:39,584 --> 01:20:41,552
to what I said earlier?

1443
01:20:41,586 --> 01:20:43,577
Do you you want
a divorce?

1444
01:20:44,789 --> 01:20:46,757
I don't know.

1445
01:20:46,791 --> 01:20:49,385
Would you?

1446
01:20:49,427 --> 01:20:52,555
I've never stopped
loving you, Millie.

1447
01:20:54,933 --> 01:20:57,401
I'm not the same
person I was.

1448
01:20:57,435 --> 01:20:59,403
I'm a very
different woman.

1449
01:20:59,437 --> 01:21:01,405
Oh I know.
I can see that.

1450
01:21:01,439 --> 01:21:03,771
I think I like
the new woman too.

1451
01:21:03,808 --> 01:21:05,435
And I am
a different man.

1452
01:21:05,477 --> 01:21:09,311
I think perhaps
I could like this new man as well.

1453
01:21:09,347 --> 01:21:12,214
Maybe the four of us
could double-date sometime.

1454
01:21:17,856 --> 01:21:20,882
- What was that for?
- Irene.

1455
01:21:20,926 --> 01:21:24,453
- What about your grandmother?
- Screw my grandmother.

1456
01:21:24,496 --> 01:21:27,431
Let's eat.

1457
01:21:31,469 --> 01:21:33,460
Right this way.

1458
01:21:36,975 --> 01:21:38,943
Your waiter will be
right with you.

1459
01:21:38,977 --> 01:21:40,945
Thank you.

1460
01:21:40,979 --> 01:21:42,947
- Thank you.
- Enjoy.

1461
01:21:42,981 --> 01:21:45,711
- It's very nice.
- I knew you'd like it.

1462
01:21:45,750 --> 01:21:48,116
Aram, could you
order me a sherry?

1463
01:21:48,153 --> 01:21:50,781
- I'll be right back.
- Oh yeah, sure.

1464
01:21:54,426 --> 01:21:56,394
Excuse me,
could you have

1465
01:21:56,428 --> 01:21:58,396
that waiter over there
serve us, please?

1466
01:21:58,430 --> 01:22:00,421
- Certainly, madam.
- Thank you.

1467
01:22:04,235 --> 01:22:07,204
Michael, table nine.

1468
01:22:09,975 --> 01:22:11,943
Good evening.

1469
01:22:11,977 --> 01:22:13,672
Good...

1470
01:22:13,712 --> 01:22:15,509
- Dad?
- Michael.

1471
01:22:15,547 --> 01:22:18,015
- Dad!
- Michael!

1472
01:22:20,085 --> 01:22:23,020
Would you like to know
tonight's specials?

1473
01:22:23,054 --> 01:22:25,545
No, I don't wanna know
tonight's specials.

1474
01:22:25,590 --> 01:22:27,558
I'd like to know
what you're doing here.

1475
01:22:27,592 --> 01:22:30,459
- I'm working.
- Working?!

1476
01:22:30,495 --> 01:22:33,828
Yes. Would you care
for a drink before dinner?

1477
01:22:33,865 --> 01:22:36,390
Yeah, I think
I could use one.

1478
01:22:36,434 --> 01:22:38,902
Crown Royal
on the rocks for me

1479
01:22:38,937 --> 01:22:41,599
and a dry sherry
for your mother.

1480
01:22:41,640 --> 01:22:43,437
Mom?

1481
01:22:43,475 --> 01:22:44,942
Yeah yeah.

1482
01:22:44,976 --> 01:22:47,638
Okay, I'll be
right back with them.

1483
01:22:47,679 --> 01:22:49,670
Dad!

1484
01:22:52,350 --> 01:22:54,318
I'm sorry I didn't
say anything.

1485
01:22:54,352 --> 01:22:57,185
- I wanted you to be surprised.
- It worked.

1486
01:22:57,222 --> 01:23:00,385
$5 million,
he's waiting on tables.

1487
01:23:00,425 --> 01:23:02,859
Yes, at least it's a job.
I thought you'd be pleased.

1488
01:23:02,894 --> 01:23:06,091
- Pleased?!
- Is anything wrong, sir?

1489
01:23:06,131 --> 01:23:08,725
Just found out my son's a lunatic.
Everything's fine.

1490
01:23:08,767 --> 01:23:10,735
Very good, sir.

1491
01:23:10,769 --> 01:23:14,136
For madam,
dry sherry.

1492
01:23:14,172 --> 01:23:16,140
- Hi, Mom.
- Hi, darling.

1493
01:23:16,174 --> 01:23:18,142
- Surprised?
- Oh yes.

1494
01:23:18,176 --> 01:23:21,407
And for the gentleman,
Crown Royal.

1495
01:23:21,446 --> 01:23:24,074
- Why, Michael?
- Why?

1496
01:23:24,115 --> 01:23:25,605
Why are you
working here?

1497
01:23:25,650 --> 01:23:28,175
It's a little
complicated to explain.

1498
01:23:28,219 --> 01:23:31,245
I should get your dinner orders
in first. Tonight's specials...

1499
01:23:31,289 --> 01:23:34,258
Never mind the specials.
Just bring me steak.

1500
01:23:34,292 --> 01:23:36,590
- Medium rare.
- I'll have the salmon.

1501
01:23:36,628 --> 01:23:38,926
- Excellent choice.
- Thank you, yes.

1502
01:23:38,963 --> 01:23:42,296
Now, salad comes with that.
Anything to start?

1503
01:23:44,436 --> 01:23:45,994
Nothing to start.

1504
01:23:50,675 --> 01:23:53,109
Couldn't you have
talked him out of this?

1505
01:23:53,144 --> 01:23:56,011
He's a man.
This is what he wants.

1506
01:23:56,047 --> 01:23:59,483
Clearing away people's dirty dishes?
That's what he wants?

1507
01:23:59,517 --> 01:24:02,918
- You said you've waited on tables.
- To make ends meet.

1508
01:24:02,954 --> 01:24:04,945
Not for the thrill of it.

1509
01:24:06,191 --> 01:24:08,591
House dressing
or vinaigrette?

1510
01:24:08,626 --> 01:24:10,685
- What's the house?
- Blue cheese and walnut.

1511
01:24:10,729 --> 01:24:12,629
- Okay, I'll have that.
- Me too.

1512
01:24:12,664 --> 01:24:15,792
Hey now, Michael, that complicated
story, I'd love to hear it.

1513
01:24:15,834 --> 01:24:18,997
Well, you know
about my divorce?

1514
01:24:19,037 --> 01:24:21,005
- Yeah.
- I told him.

1515
01:24:21,039 --> 01:24:23,007
I'm sorry.

1516
01:24:23,041 --> 01:24:26,374
The day the divorce became final,
I was feeling pretty down.

1517
01:24:26,411 --> 01:24:29,539
I can understand that. Your wife running
off with the ball player.

1518
01:24:29,581 --> 01:24:32,709
If it had at least been
a real good ball player... you know?

1519
01:24:32,751 --> 01:24:34,946
I mean, your woman leaves you
for George Brett

1520
01:24:34,986 --> 01:24:36,954
or Don Mattingly,
you kind of understand.

1521
01:24:36,988 --> 01:24:40,515
But this guy never batted
over 260 in his career.

1522
01:24:40,558 --> 01:24:42,526
Couldn't hit an
inside slider if his life

1523
01:24:42,560 --> 01:24:44,187
depended on it,
and his fielding...

1524
01:24:44,229 --> 01:24:46,891
I understand. The man is not gonna
make the Hall of Fame.

1525
01:24:46,931 --> 01:24:49,923
Anyway, I was really
feeling low,

1526
01:24:49,968 --> 01:24:51,936
and I happened to pass
by this restaurant.

1527
01:24:51,970 --> 01:24:54,905
I thought to myself,
"Okay, maybe I'll go inside.

1528
01:24:54,939 --> 01:24:57,737
I might have a nice dinner.
I'll feel a little better"

1529
01:24:57,776 --> 01:24:59,471
And darned
if it didn't work!

1530
01:24:59,511 --> 01:25:03,345
The food was terrific,
I had some really nice wine,

1531
01:25:03,381 --> 01:25:05,815
and when I finished,
I really felt better.

1532
01:25:05,850 --> 01:25:08,876
You know, like the world
wasn't such a terrible place after all.

1533
01:25:08,920 --> 01:25:11,480
And I felt grateful.

1534
01:25:11,523 --> 01:25:13,491
I wanted
to thank somebody

1535
01:25:13,525 --> 01:25:16,255
for the terrific meal I had that just
cheered me up so much.

1536
01:25:16,294 --> 01:25:19,263
But who?
Who would you thank?

1537
01:25:19,297 --> 01:25:22,528
I don't know,
the waiter, the chef.

1538
01:25:22,567 --> 01:25:25,331
Them? Sure,
but they're not the only ones.

1539
01:25:25,370 --> 01:25:27,338
What about the people
who wash the dishes?

1540
01:25:27,372 --> 01:25:29,863
What about the people
who sweep up?

1541
01:25:29,908 --> 01:25:31,876
Or the cocktail pianist?

1542
01:25:31,910 --> 01:25:34,310
What about the fisherman
who caught the fish I ate?

1543
01:25:34,345 --> 01:25:36,313
The farmer who grew
the lettuce,

1544
01:25:36,347 --> 01:25:38,474
the people who picked
the grapes for the wine?

1545
01:25:38,516 --> 01:25:41,314
What about the miner
who dug out the silver for the cutlery?

1546
01:25:41,352 --> 01:25:43,718
I mean, if you add them all up,
thousands of people

1547
01:25:43,755 --> 01:25:46,451
worked to make that meal
I enjoyed so much possible.

1548
01:25:46,491 --> 01:25:48,459
- Pepper?
- Thank you.

1549
01:25:48,493 --> 01:25:50,688
That's what work is.
Doing something

1550
01:25:50,728 --> 01:25:53,595
that makes life a little bit nicer
for other people.

1551
01:25:53,631 --> 01:25:56,259
You can't just go through life
without doing something

1552
01:25:56,301 --> 01:25:58,997
back for them.
I mean, Dad, it's not right.

1553
01:25:59,037 --> 01:26:02,473
So on my way out,
I asked the maitre d'

1554
01:26:02,507 --> 01:26:05,908
if they had any job openings...
here I am.

1555
01:26:05,944 --> 01:26:07,468
Working as a waiter?

1556
01:26:07,512 --> 01:26:09,912
A person has to work.

1557
01:26:09,948 --> 01:26:11,848
I know that!

1558
01:26:11,883 --> 01:26:13,942
I've always
known that, Michael.

1559
01:26:13,985 --> 01:26:15,953
Aram, you don't seem
to understand.

1560
01:26:15,987 --> 01:26:18,387
Michael had to prove to himself
that he wasn't you.

1561
01:26:18,423 --> 01:26:21,620
Work for you is everything,
so for him it had to be nothing.

1562
01:26:21,659 --> 01:26:24,594
- Now, he was dumb.
- She's right, I was dumb.

1563
01:26:24,629 --> 01:26:26,597
Well, you both were dumb.

1564
01:26:26,631 --> 01:26:29,896
I wish I had some special ability
or a talent in some field,

1565
01:26:29,934 --> 01:26:32,164
but if I have,
I haven't found it yet,

1566
01:26:32,203 --> 01:26:33,761
and maybe I never will.

1567
01:26:35,440 --> 01:26:38,671
I'm sorry if I haven't
turned out the way you wanted, Dad.

1568
01:26:38,710 --> 01:26:41,406
I'm sorry if I'm not
the son you wanted,

1569
01:26:41,446 --> 01:26:43,414
but this is me.

1570
01:26:43,448 --> 01:26:45,643
I think your dinner
should be ready now.

1571
01:26:47,652 --> 01:26:49,643
Michael.

1572
01:26:55,093 --> 01:26:58,062
If all the fathers
of all the people

1573
01:26:58,096 --> 01:27:00,064
that ever won
a Nobel prize

1574
01:27:00,098 --> 01:27:02,066
were here tonight,

1575
01:27:02,100 --> 01:27:04,068
every one of them
would envy the way I feel

1576
01:27:04,102 --> 01:27:06,127
about my son right now.

1577
01:27:10,308 --> 01:27:12,606
Sir, if you are pleased
with our service,

1578
01:27:12,644 --> 01:27:14,908
a simple gratuity
would suffice.

1579
01:27:23,888 --> 01:27:25,856
I have to go
to the Palisades today.

1580
01:27:25,890 --> 01:27:27,858
I have this tax appeal
on the new shop.

1581
01:27:27,892 --> 01:27:30,360
- I'll see you tonight for dinner.
- All right, dear.

1582
01:27:30,395 --> 01:27:33,023
- So what are you gonna be doing today?
- I think I'll play

1583
01:27:33,064 --> 01:27:36,227
tennis with Michael and then maybe
go to the track with Walter.

1584
01:27:36,267 --> 01:27:39,395
- Okay, I'll see you tonight.
- Okay, bye-bye.

1585
01:27:39,437 --> 01:27:42,201
- Bye, Mom, have a good day.
- Goodbye, sweetheart.

1586
01:27:42,240 --> 01:27:45,175
Hi Dad, I'm sorry I can't play tennis.
I gotta get to work.

1587
01:27:45,209 --> 01:27:46,836
- Why so early?
- Oh, it's chaos.

1588
01:27:46,878 --> 01:27:49,574
Two busboys quit the restaurant.
We're short of staff.

1589
01:27:49,614 --> 01:27:52,640
Maybe I should apply for a job there,
get to work again.

1590
01:27:52,684 --> 01:27:54,549
You do work.
You handle my investments.

1591
01:27:54,585 --> 01:27:56,576
Oh, a couple
of phone calls a week.

1592
01:27:56,621 --> 01:27:58,987
Yeah, whatever.
My money's earning twice as much.

1593
01:27:59,023 --> 01:28:00,991
By the way, are you
all right for cash?

1594
01:28:01,025 --> 01:28:02,993
I told you,
when I need I'll ask.

1595
01:28:03,027 --> 01:28:04,995
- Yeah, but you never do.
- Oh Lord.

1596
01:28:05,029 --> 01:28:08,089
- I'll see you later
- All right, kid, bye.

1597
01:28:08,132 --> 01:28:10,100
Oh, Michael.

1598
01:28:11,970 --> 01:28:15,167
Do you ever stop and think
that while you're running around

1599
01:28:15,206 --> 01:28:17,902
every day in that restaurant
carrying those heavy trays

1600
01:28:17,942 --> 01:28:21,400
in and out of that steamy kitchen,
I'm just sitting by your pool,

1601
01:28:21,446 --> 01:28:23,710
drinking your booze,
eating your food,

1602
01:28:23,748 --> 01:28:26,376
in general having one hell of a time
with your money?

1603
01:28:26,417 --> 01:28:29,545
Yeah, sometimes I think
about that.

1604
01:28:29,587 --> 01:28:31,612
How does that
make you feel?

1605
01:28:31,656 --> 01:28:33,419
I love it.

1606
01:28:35,293 --> 01:28:38,626
I'll see you later.

1607
01:30:45,089 --> 01:30:45,953
English - R1

